text: Laura Di Muzio (born 20 March 1990) is a French rugby union and rugby sevens player, and television commentator. She played for Lille Métropole rugby club villeneuvois. She was captain of the team, and champion of France in 2016. She was a television commentator for the 2018 Women's Six Nations Championship, and 2019 Women's Rugby Super Series. == References == == Other websites == * #10 Laura di Muzio - Championne de France de rugby, à 26 ans elle crée son entreprise pour vivre de son sport Pourquoi pas moi, 3/12/2020 Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:French rugby union players Category:Rugby sevens players Category:French television personalities Category:People from Nord Category:Sportspeople from Hauts-de-France
